review_blob: At first I wasnt a fan but then this nut brown ale grew on me.  Very nutty flavor but not overpowering and I enjoy it greatly.  Ive had both bottle and on tap and I dont know if its the atmosphere but I prefer it on Tap. (not to mention its only $1 a frosty mug at my local watering hole)
beer_name: New Glarus Fat Squirrel Nut Brown Ale

review_blob: One of my favorite Stouts ever.  Very dark color with coffee undertones that increase towards the finish.

Nice red color, aroma of sweet and tart cherries.  Perfect for a special occasion or to share on a romantic night with your significant other.  Doesnt have a traditional beer taste so women who dont like beer will even love this one
